text: Garfield County is a county in the U.S. state of Nebraska. As of the 2020 census, 1,813 people lived there. The county seat is Burwell. It was founded in 1884 and named after James A. Garfield, 20th President of the United States. ==References== Category:1880s establishments in Nebraska Category:1884 establishments in the United States Category:Nebraska counties
title: Garfield County, Nebraska
